A '''temporary skill drain''' is are effects from [[item]]s, [[monster]]s, [[weapon]] and [[ammunition]] [[special attacks]] or passive abilities, interactions with [[scenery]], or the environment that temporarily lowers a player's level in one or more [[skills]]. This can be counter-acted with [[temporary skill boost]]s or [[stat restoration]].

Skill drain can cause the player to no longer be able to do certain actions. For example, lowering your [[Cooking]] level below 25 means it is not possible to make [[stew]] until the stat has restored to its required level to make. The [[Rapid Restore]] [[Prayer]] can be used to reduce the stat change timer from 60 seconds to 30, making drained stat restoration occur twice as fast.

Some skill drains stack, drinking multiple [[wine]]s will lower [[Attack]] by 2 for every one consumed, however some combat related special attacks and spells will only apply when the stat is at or above the unchanged level.

On the tables below, CurrentLevel refers to the left-side number on the skills interface and StaticLevel refers to the right-side.

